cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with analyzing and discovering common latent structures in 3D shapes using neural networks, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of probe functions and semantic understanding of shapes suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). The segmentation and keypoint selection applications also suggest a possible connection to natural language processing (CL).
